In Book V. Aeneas reaches Italy on the anni- versary of his father‘s death, and celebrates elabor- ate funeral games in his honour. Juno persuades the matrons to set fire to the ships, but Aeneas prays for rain, which stays the flames, and then, leaving the less adventurous among his followers behind, he sets sail for Italy.

In Book VI. Aeneas lands 31 Cumae, and with the help of the Sibyl discovers the ‘ golden bough,’ which is a passport through the under world. Through it he passes, guided by the Sibyl, and finally finds Anchises, who points 0111 10 him the souls of those who are destined to become great Romans and describes their future fortunes, after which Aeneas returns safely to the upper air.
